---
// Problem section — the data asymmetry
---

<section id="problem" class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Section label -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
      <span class="w-6 h-px bg-[var(--mars-orange)]"></span>
      <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-[var(--text-muted)] uppercase tracking-[3px]">The Problem</span>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-mono font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4 tracking-tight">
      They know you better than you know yourself.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] max-w-2xl mb-12 leading-relaxed">
      Corporations have spent decades building structured datasets about every person on the internet. You have none of that about yourself. As AI gets more capable, this gap becomes a chasm.
    </p>

    <!-- Problem cards -->
    <div class="space-y-px">
      {[
        {
          num: "01",
          title: "Data asymmetry",
          desc: "Corporations invest billions structuring data about you — you don't even have access to most of it. The agent that knows you best isn't yours."
        },
        {
          num: "02",
          title: "Context-blind AI",
          desc: "AI agents are powerful but useless without personal context. Your data is scattered across dozens of siloed apps. Your agent knows none of it."
        },
        {
          num: "03",
          title: "No guided path",
          desc: "Learning AI has no guided path. You either figure it out alone, get overwhelmed by options, or never start at all."
        }
      ].map(({ num, title, desc }) => (
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 sm:gap-6 px-5 sm:px-6 py-5 bg-[var(--surface-1)] border border-[var(--border-subtle)] first:rounded-t-xl last:rounded-b-xl hover:border-[var(--border-medium)] transition-colors">
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-[var(--mars-orange)] mt-0.5 shrink-0">{num}</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-mono font-bold text-sm text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-1">{title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">{desc}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-8 max-w-2xl italic">
      The gap between what AI could know about you and what it actually knows &mdash; that's the problem we're closing.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
